special topics in group theory page 1 department colloquium thursday november 17 4 15pm building 380 room 380 w daniel bump stanford university whittaker functions and demazure characters abstract the affine hecke algebra is a famous ring that appears in two seemingly unrelated settings 1 the representation theory of p adic groups like gl n over the p adic field and 2 the topology of complex flag varieties we will explain how kazhdan and lusztig used this coincidence in a spectacular way we will explain a new context for this fact in a sort of calculus of relations between whittaker functions which are special functions on p adic groups this is joint work with ben brubaker and tony licata
